26/04/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The ruling Social Democratic Party (PSD) plans to select a presidential candidate in June, said PSD secretary general Dan Matei Agathonon on Saturday (24 April). 
Also Saturday, PSD nominated two candidates for local elections in Muntenia and Oltenia. 
But Prime Minister Adrian Nastase says it is too early to choose nominees. 
(Rompres, Nine O'clock - 25/04/04)
